  "title": "Manufacturing Engineer (CNC Programming) #JTL",
  "description": "<p>• Perform process planning and fixture & gauge designs<br />• Handle quotations and program management<br />• Apply Six Sigma/Lean Manufacturing methodologies for continuous process improvements<br />• Planning and scheduling of ERP system</p><p>• Prepare NC programs, including tooling design and selection, for 5-axis milling on materials ranging from Aluminium, Titanium to Inconel 718.</p><p>• Probe programming for error proofing, datum setting, dimension check etc.</p><p>• Control of machining cycle time within target including all in-machine activities such as probing, machining, appropriate cutter checks etc.</p><p>• Control overall costs for machining taking into consideration cycle time and cost of cutters.</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>- Minimum Degree in Engineering</p><p>- Preferably with 3-5 years of relevant manufacturing engineering</p><p>- Experience in Six Sigma/Lean Manufacturing methodologies</p><p>- Experience in CNC programming </p><p><strong>Interested candidates please send in your resume to:</strong></p><p><strong>Topaz Liang Huimin (CEI No. R1104500), email to: topaz@recruitexpress.com.sg</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>EA License No: 99C4599</strong></p>",
